Skip redundant CI runs between phase transitions

tl;dr

--if-dirty only skipped on a fully clean tree, which never happens during
active development. Now it stores and compares git status snapshots — same
snapshot means nothing changed since CI last passed, so skip. Moved from
shell logic in bin/ci to lib/ci.py routed through bin/flow ci.

- lib/ci.py: CI wrapper with snapshot-based dirty checking and JSON output
- bin/ci: Remove --if-dirty and sentinel logic (moved to lib/ci.py)
- .claude/skills/commit/SKILL.md: Step 0 uses bin/flow ci --if-dirty
- skills/code/SKILL.md: Final sweep uses bin/flow ci --if-dirty
- skills/commit/SKILL.md: Same update for plugin commit skill
- skills/review/SKILL.md: Pre-transition gate uses bin/flow ci --if-dirty
- skills/security/SKILL.md: Per-fix step uses bin/flow ci --if-dirty
- .claude/settings.json: Narrow permission from bin/ci* to exact bin/ci
- lib/init-setup.py: Same permission narrowing in runtime source
- skills/init/SKILL.md: Same permission narrowing in reference docs
- tests/test_ci.py: New tests for snapshot-based dirty checking
- tests/test_bin_ci.py: Remove migrated --if-dirty tests
- tests/test_bin_flow.py: Add FLOW_CI_RUNNING guard to prevent recursion
- tests/test_permissions.py: Update regex test for exact bin/ci match
